Auto-Purger

The purpose of the auto-purger is to remove non-condensable gases from the system without requiring the system to be manually opened. The auto-purger consists of the following components: water bubbler, foul gas line, liquid line, suction line, water line, drain line, and remote purge point solenoid valves. The auto-purger removes non-condensable gases by refrigerating the foul gas so that the ammonia vapor condenses to liquid and can be returned to the system. The non-condensable gases are removed from the system through the water bubbler. Under normal conditions, the auto-purger contains small quantities of ammonia and water. 



1.2.5 Safety Systems



Ammonia Detection System

The detection system is interlocked with the refrigeration system controls as follows:

Two (2) ammonia detectors are installed within the machinery room;

If the ammonia concentration exceeds 25 ppm, visual alarms will be initiated outside the machinery room; in addition, exhaust fan 1 will be activated;

If the ammonia concentration exceeds 125 ppm, exhaust fan 2 will be activated;

If the ammonia concentration exceeds 150 ppm, audible alarms will be initiated outside the machinery room;

If the ammonia concentration exceeds 5,000 ppm, the refrigeration machinery inside the machinery room will be de-energized;

An ammonia detector is installed in each refrigerated docks/rooms;

If the ammonia concentration exceeds 25 ppm, visual alarms will be initiated;

If the ammonia concentration exceeds 35 ppm, audible alarms will be initiated;

